<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/195</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GMM1" type="from">Major
                                        Grimprel</persName> of the French High Commission to the
                                    Chairman of the War Trade Board</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">McCormick</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-02">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName></hi>: The Government of the Republic advises
                                that, at the request of the Swiss Legation, it has informed the
                                Netherland Government that the Dutch ships now held in the United
                                States, which may proceed to Cette for the transportation of
                                supplies to Switzerland, would neither be detained nor requisitioned
                                    <pb facs="0560" n="1394" xml:id="pg_1394"/> by France, but would
                                be allowed to continue on their course in accordance with the
                                agreements reached in the meantime with Holland.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GMM1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">M. Grimprel</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>